"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"> Even in spite of the growing availability of privacy coins like Monero and Zcash, criminals continue to use Bitcoin because of the abundance of Bitcoin-to-fiat offramps. Banks and money service businesses should pay attention to high-risk transactions originating from BATMs that lack proper AML compliance.”\\n\\n## Bitcoin cleaner than fiat?\\n\\nEven though the crypto sector is still routinely maligned by members of the mainstream media that claim that digital currencies are still, by and large, being used by bad actors for nefarious reasons — such as terrorist financing, drug trade, etc. — Jefferies told Cointelegraph that as per his company’s latest research, cryptocurrencies are considerably cleaner than their reputation would suggest:\\n\\n> “The reality is that criminal use of Bitcoin and other cryptocurrencies is very low, less than 0.2% of the funds accepted by exchanges is directly from criminal sources.”\\n\\n***Related: [Criminal Activity in Crypto: The Fact, the Fiction and the Context](https://cointelegraph.com/news/criminal-activity-in-crypto-the-fact-the-fiction-and-the-context)***\",\"timestamp\":1639122074,\"title\":\"Even in spite of the growing availability of privacy\"},\"digest\":\"ADIyeKcnQyfA9_Dhb-rwknUMbppFzyrIpp6OeF3HlEA\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x96A7136A24B3132c359ED5C28e1507D5AE738d33\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"QCK9r5mcvo4tqtnKe17X5LH0WIcN0LTRyt1Mf9A1kRc\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"X--0EXkE-Vm6Kt0JeBoiALekH4-a9IOQf-Q8jWzm4W4\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"s4AwfCHtUl0UR7imqBlI0YXHAOAFe9xQajBPYzXu_UUPRnUWy8obmWr_AlE0HFCxNBiB0Tt-KINgtqfpbOaliw\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0xcc8ad8ece14190e800f39a7095e37fb6197e16e270b6c30ebec27ed1efc05e657fec3114da7181b4afad31a98a3178970d77e6d7b9a1122da377b4ad88891bad1c\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\